BT 1 0 0 1 0 99 Tm 12 TL /F1 9 Tf 0 0 0 rg (Granovetter's threshold model of collective behavior \(Granovetter 1978, American Journal of Sociology\): individuals have) Tj T* (private thresholds for joining collective action \(riot, revolution, social movement\). Each individual joins when the fraction of) Tj T* (others who have already joined exceeds their personal threshold. The equilibrium of the system -- whether a riot spreads or) Tj T* (fizzles -- depends on the distribution of these thresholds across the population. This is the Wike Coherence Law at social) Tj T* (scale: individual thresholds are individual gamma_c values; the population distribution of thresholds determines the system) Tj T* (gamma_c; when the environmental perturbation \(provocative event, information cascade\) exceeds the system gamma_c,) Tj T* (coherent collective action emerges \(phase transition\). Durkheim's "collective effervescence" \(1912\) and modern social) Tj T* (contagion \(Christakis & Fowler 2009\) are the same phenomenon, precisely formalized by Granovetter's threshold model) Tj T* (and by the Wike framework's gamma_c.) Tj T* ET
